        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:43PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Blowing Rock, or 5 miles southeast of Blowing Rock
In Caldwell County, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blowing Rock In Caldwell County, Patterson, Upton, and Globe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
